State Driver Licensing Agencies

must query the Clearinghouse prior to completing licensing transactions

The following information is made available in the Clearinghouse:
Positive DOT drug & alcohol results
Reports of drivers who were under the influence of drugs/alcohol while on duty
Alcohol use within 8 hours of an accident or until the post-accident report is complete
Refusal of a drug/alcohol test
The Clearinghouse must be queried, or checked, before hiring a new driver, as well as annually throughout each driver's employment. Information contained in the Clearinghouse is subject to both the Privacy Act and the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA). Before a company or their TPA can query the Clearinghouse, they must get driver consent.

Until January 6, 2023, TPAs and employers must query the
Clearinghouse and request background check information
from past DOT-regulated employers.

Violation data is available in the Clearinghouse for 5 years, or until the return-to-duty process is complete

